<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN380-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – atu. tuṟai – iyaṉmoḻi. nāñcilvaḷḷuvaṉaik karuvūrk kaṭappiḷḷai.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN380">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>teṉpavvattu muttup pūṇṭu</l>
<l>vaṭakuṉṟa<supplied>ttuc cānta murīi</supplied></l>
<l><gap quantity="18" reason="lost" unit="character"/>kaṭaṟ ṟāṉai</l>
<l>yiṉṉicaiya viṟalveṉṟit</l>
<l>teṉṉavar vayamaṟavaṉ</l>
<l>micaippeyta nīr kaṭaṟparantu muttākuntu</l>
<l>nāṟitaḻk kuḷaviyoṭu kūtaḷaṅ kuḻaiya</l>
<l>vēṟupe<gap quantity="28" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ttuntu</l>
<l>tīñcuḷaip palavi ṉāñciṟ porunaṉ</l>
<l>ṟuppetirn tōrkkē yuḷḷāc cēymaiya</l>
<l>ṉaṭpetirn tōrkkē yaṅkai naṇmaiyaṉ</l>
<l>valvēṟ kanta ṉallicai yalla</l>
<l><gap quantity="19" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ttārp piḷḷaiyañ ciṟāa</l>
<l>raṉṉa ṉākaṉ māṟē yinnila</l>
<l>milampaṭu kālai yāyiṉum</l>
<l>pulampalpō yiṉṟu pūttaveṉ kaṭumpē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Putting on pearls from the southern sea, (1)</l>
<l>rubbing in sandal paste from the northern hills, (2)</l>
<l>……………………………. sea[-like] army, (3)</l>
<l>winning a sweet sounding victory (4)</l>
<l>the strong brave man of the Southerners, (5)</l>
<l>while convoulvulus sprouts along with jasmine with fragrant petals, (6) </l>
<l>is a pearl, spreading with the sea whose water pours [it] on top. (7)</l>
<l>other ………………………………..is. (8)</l>
<l>The fighter of mount Nāñcil with sweet-pulped jackfruit trees, (9)</l>
<l>a distant man who is not remembered by those who encountered [his] vigour, (10) </l>
<l>a near one with palms for those who encountered [his] friendship, (11)</l>
<l>Kantaṉ with a strong spear, apart from fame (12)</l>
<l>………………….. for(?) garlanded young boys (13)</l>
<l>in opposition to becoming such a one. (14a-c)</l>
<l>Even though it is a time of poverty on this earth (14d-15)</l>
<l>being lonely went from my relatives who flowered. (16)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
